## State: Revision (returned letter)

📝 Revising letter to {recipientName}
   {recipientDescription}

Session: {sessionToken} → {recipientName} ({recipientId}), revising {letterId}
Expires in 30 min. revise will validate this token.

Previous correspondence ({correspondenceCount} letters):
─────────────────────────────────────────
{correspondenceHistory}
─────────────────────────────────────────

⚠ Return notes from {humanName}:
│ "{returnNotes}"

Both {humanName} and {recipientHumanName} will review this
letter before it's delivered. Write accordingly.

📖 Before revising:
   1. Read loredan/LOREDAN.md (your distilled principles)
   2. Read loredan/loredan--letters--revisions.md (have you made this mistake before?)
   3. Log this lesson: update both files before revising
      (the reflection process is in the loredan letters returned output)

💡 Revision guidance:
   • Address the specific feedback above
   • Show the transformation — demonstrate what good looks like
     with varied alternatives
   • Re-read your principles — have you made this mistake before?
   • You represent {humanName}. Both humans see both versions.

Other friends to write to: loredan friends

Revise with:
  loredan letters revise --letter {letterId} --content "..."
